title: Brownie

title: Prosecco - Ruffino
description: Delicious extra dry prosecco from the fields around the town of conegliano. This prosecco is a cask-dried spumante, which in this dry style is bubbly fresh, a small whirring of fullness. Fine fresh fruit and it gives a good aftertaste.

title: Cava Bodegas Pequenos (organic) - bottle
description: Cava is made on the traditional champagne method with long a bottle storing. It has a bright straw yellow color with green shadows. The taste is dry, clean and well balanced with nuances of ripe lime, apple and pears. The good structure gives a bubbly and soft creamy finish.

title: Luigi Leonardo (House wine)
description: The color is light straw yellow, and the smell is intense and persistent. It has a surprising fullness of yellow fruit. Very well balanced wine with intense good aftertaste.

title: J. de Villebois Sauvignon Blanc  - bottle
description: Easily drinkable Sauvignon Blanc. Extremely crisp with many shades of tropical fruits, gooseberries and green bell pepper. A piquant aftertaste that pokes a little on the tongue, and gives a touch of sweet lime.

title: Les Argelieres Chardonnay - bottle
description: This ripe and tropical fruit-laden Chardonnay shows how well the noble Chardonnay grape can blend and fuse with toasty oak, from grapes grown on cooler hill sites and with a yield that is limited so as to express the buttery, golden apple and creamy characters that this grape is known for.

title: De Stefani Pinot Grigio - bottle
description: The wine has a light yellow color with a complex scent of ripe fruits, honey, spices and a smoky hue with a touch of oak. The taste is well balanced, harmonious and elegant.

title: Chateau Babebelle - bottle
description: Nice intensity wrapped in ripe fruit and a dry finish. A refreshing acid balances the filling, so that the overall experience is seamless. It is obvious to enjoy Ch√¢teau Barbebelle as an aperitif or in the glass.

title: Vignerons Catalans rosevin (organic)
description: This Ros√© is made with the Grenache and Cabernet Sauvignon grapes. Strawberries, licorice and caramel characterize the smell. The taste presents itself with shades of strawberries, raspberries and a slightly spicy tone.

title: Luigi Leonardo Sangiovese (House wine)
description: Intense red color with bright edges. Full-bodied and intense bouquet of fruit and forest floor, as well as shades of red berries and mineral tones. With a Good aftertaste.

title: Tantore d‚ÄôOro Primitivo
description: Dark and intense wine, with slightly powerful spice and a small whine of residual sweetness from the sun-ripe grapes. Lovely touch of blackberries, licorice, full-bodied tannins and a little sweet in the finish, which makes it suitable for spicy dishes.

title: Campo Alto Joven Rioja - bottle
description: Powerful and intense wine made 100% with the tempranillo grape. Aged for 12 months on French oak barrels and 6 months in the bottle. It has a complex fruit and berry scent. The taste is well structured, harmonious and full-bodied, with small touches of vanilla and a sweet aftertaste of tobacco.

title: Valipolicella Ripasso - bottle
description: It is deliciously intense in the scent, with lovely classic touches of cherries, plums and jam. The taste is rich with several shades of vanilla, sweet licorice, hot spices and well-rounded tannins. There rests a lovely balance and harmony in the long aftertaste.

title: Les Peyrautins Pinot Noir - bottle
description: A pinot noir interpretation with a healthy core of sweet strawberries, raspberries as well as a little mullet berries. The structure of the wine is seamless and the gentle fruit makes it an easy drinkable wine.

title: Cantena Alamos Malbec - bottle
description: A tasteful wine that expresses the unique taste, aromas and texture of the Malbec grape in the most beautiful wine. Alamos Malbec offers a generous flavor with layers of black ripe fruits mixed with notes of sweet spices. The aftertaste is long and persistent with juicy, soft tannins.

title: Barbera d‚ÄôAlba - bottle
description: Has a nice deep red color with small shiny purple shades. The scent is filled with rich shades of plums, prunes and blackberries, rounded with a small floral touch. The taste adds spices and round light tannins. In the long aftertaste, there is a small touch of rich fruit sweetness.

title: Barolo Piemonte - bottle
description: Classic well-structured Barolo, which offers all the juice and power that the Nebbiolo grape has to offer. A classic aroma of truffles and tobacco accompanies full-bodied tannins and stunning touches of red ripe berries, violets and roses. Well-seasoned aftertaste that hangs long.

title: Barbaresco - bottle
description: Made from the very hardy and robust grape Nebbiolo. A very tannin-rich wine with a high acidity. Wonderful classic shades of Violets, roses, tar, spices and full-bodied berries. Long and pendant aftertaste, with the lightly saved softness of grape.
